# .env.ops.local — gitignored ops credentials that scripts/db/*.mts use to operate against PROD.
# Copy this to `.env.ops.local` (already gitignored via `.env*.local`) and fill in the real values.
# This is the single place the agent's ops wrappers read prod secrets from — keeps them out of the
# command line (which trips secret-exploration guards) and avoids `vercel env pull` (sensitive vars
# come back blank). Twin of how scripts/db/sql.mts reads SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN from .env.local.

# PROD cron auth — used by scripts/db/cron.mts to trigger crons against https://app.getticket.ai.
# This is the Production CRON_SECRET from Vercel (prophet project). If it's a "Sensitive" var you
# can't read back, rotate it: set a new value in Vercel prod env + redeploy, then paste the same
# value here.
CRON_SECRET=

# OPTIONAL — only if the prod domain ever sits behind Vercel Deployment Protection. The project's
# "Protection Bypass for Automation" secret; sent as the x-vercel-protection-bypass header.
# VERCEL_PROTECTION_BYPASS=
